    [ctns_front]
X-Intercept and Y-Intercept<br>Linear Function
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
The $$y$$-intercept of a function is the value of $$y$$ when $$x=0$$. The $$x$$-intercept of a function is the value of $$x$$ when $$y=0$$. 
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]
